        <p>(Optional) It is not mandatory to create any template pages in order to have<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> Side</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> Top</MadCap:conditionalText> Navigation output. However, template pages can be particularly useful, especially if you want the same content to automatically show up at the bottom or top of topics. They can also useful if you want your Home page's design to be much different from that of the rest of your topics. So if you would like to incorporate one or more template pages, create them. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Template-Pages/Process/Creating-Template-Pages.htm">Creating Template Pages</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
